    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory biannual reapplication for all firearm licences",
        "additional_details": "After the recent tragic events in Plymouth shootings, it essential that we establish if there are people who currently hold firearms licences that should not be in possession of a firearm.\r\n \r\nWhat we want the Government to do is make all current licence holders renew their licenses within the next 6 months.\r\n \r\nA medical and mental health assessment must be completed, paid for by the applicant, in order to have the licence renewed. This process is to be made a biannual requirement for all licences.",
        "background": "All individuals that currently hold firearms licences should be required to reapply for these in the next six months, and must undertake a medical and mental health check before having a licence reissued. This should be made a biannual process going forward.",
